1. Choose Real-life Problems (examples below):
  Number of emails received per hour.
  Number of customer arrivals in a shop per minute.
  Number of printing errors per page in a book.
2. Set Up Excel Table:
  Column A: Values of x (number of events)
  Column B: Use the POISSON.DIST function:
    =POISSON.DIST(x, λ, FALSE) for exact probability
    =POISSON.DIST(x, λ, TRUE) for cumulative probability
